reviews: This hostel is fantastic! All of the staff have been amazing, very friendly and professional, lots of fun, and very helpful. Particularly Lys at reception, and this one very kind security guard who’s name I believe was Momo. Lys was super cool and made the stay that much nicer. Momo rescued us from some sketchy characters who were bothering us outside the hostel late at night, and he was really funny. The other reception staff were also super cool but I don’t have any of their names. It was just a great time, the facility was very nice, the hangout room was perfect, the social events were awesome including the night club downstairs. Also, despite the odd people you tend to encounter at night in any big city, the area seemed relatively safe. My friend I made here has stayed in 8 different Paris hostels and said this was the best one BY FAR. Not to mention the price was very reasonable. I would recommend this hostel to anyone staying in Paris.

Hello 👋! It was okay in general, apart there was no locker nor fridge and also no plug-in in my bed. Guests and hosts were nice but not as friendly as in the UK "ST. CHRISTOPHER INN FOR YOUTH" in Scotland, Edinburgh 🇬🇧 👀 😇. I forgot to add there was no lift / elevator ...! One advantage was the location near the metro 🚇.

AVOID AVOID this place AT ALL COST!
THIS PLACE IS DANGEROUS!
In the middle of my sleep one of the receptionists pulled me out of my bed aggressively all of a sudden I was then severely mistreated for 18 hours by authorities, the staff then destroyed my new suitcase, they damaged my computer, stole my bankcards, among other important things, then they refused to give me my money back from my rent money that I paid for a few days, it was my last money for the months, I was then on the ice cold streets in Paris not knowing where to sleep! Until today I don t know why I was aggressed while I was sleeping I didn t do anything wrong at all and why my important belongings were intentionally destroyed and stolen! As a foreigner without bank cards in a foreign country I couldn t get then any money out because my banks don t exist in Paris, I could not eat then for days and didn t know how to get back to my country! It was PURE TORTURE! Severe charges are pressed with the police and with the coroner! I will not cease to persecute them until I get a decent compensation back from this extreme mistreatment and dangerous torture! Even my expensive Mac computer is damaged now! Severe charges are pressed!
AVOID! AVOID! this place at all cost!

Worst hostel I've been. Shower drain is blocked, so you better like having your feet in the water of the previous person that just showered. Toilet was a bit dirty, Pillow sheet torned, Blanked torned, noisy bed, broken locker. Asked the service to use another bed(in order to get a functioning locker) , but apparently, it was already reserved, 2days later the other bed was still available. People going there are a little too party type.

Beautiful spot but not very practical for transportation. You have to walk a bit.

My friend and I were excited to stay here after seen all the good reviews but we were quickly disappointed. All 4 nights we stayed, we couldn’t sleep more than 3-4 hrs because it was very noisy even at 4am. Every single day people gathered outside the hostile and made so much noise. Not getting adequate sleep ruined our 4 day stay in Paris since we were always tired and didn’t want to return to the hostile. The bathrooms were dirty and the beds uncomfortable. Reconsider staying here if u want to rest and enjoy ur stay in Paris. I do not recommend this hostile.

A perfect place to stay when you travel alone. Cheap, clean, safe. It seems like there is a lot of other "alone travelers" here. Its also a resturant with a nice place to sit outside nearby the river. It seems like a social, relaxed place, but also a place where you perfektly can sit alone. Really liked this place! Recomenned! The staff is also very helpful, and gives good service. And ofc: Its Paris! I love Paris.

The staff were friendly and the food in the bar delicious but some major problems at this hostel and will not be revisiting. We’ve stayed a dozens of hostels, a fair few St Christophers also. This one was far below standard.

Cleanliness:
- Showers grotty. Walls weren’t wiped during out entire stay with mud streaks and hair stuck to them.
- Signs everywhere advertising ‘cleaners on site 18 hours a day’ while it took them over 12 hours to mop up vomit in the hallway that has been reported numerous times. Even then, it wasn’t cleaned up properly.

Communal Spaces:
- Access to the communal spaces was limited due to the chill out area being the home to over 10 trolleys of dirty bedding leaving slim room for guests.
- The bar advertised as being included with the hostel was booked for private events during our stay limiting our ability to socialites, eat and drink within the hostel. This is one of the key features of a St Christopher’s and is advertised as a reason for booking. Not when it’s not available.
- Communal bathrooms were subpar with soap dispensers empty, no hand dryers and hair dryers only available in the female toilets which is extremely sexist.
- No where to fill up water bottles, no communal fountain or tap
- We understand some hostels don’t provide kitchens due to having to maintain and clean them but the is often a fridge available to guests needing to store items. This was lacking.

Breakfast:
- Not worth the paper it’s advertised on.
- Watery coffee that never gets refilled. Stale week old bread buns and fruit that never gets replenished. Breakfast consisted of cornflakes and orange juice, we ended up just eating at local bakery’s.
- No dairy milk alternatives for those that may be intolerant or vegan when the main elements of the lacking breakfast are dairy based.

Being 40, I felt really old going to a hostel but the double I got on the 6th floor was great, with a fabulous balcony overlooking a kids playground and the canal close by. This is a very cute part of Paris and only ten minutes in a cab to Gare du Nord. The reason I’ve not given 5* is because the shower flooded the bathroom making it a bit of a slip risk but the front desk staff were brilliant and couldn’t do enough to help, even with the most basic of questions. Everyone I encountered working there was friendly, helpful and generous. Between that and a couple of great local restaurants close by this is a gem.

Stayed here on an interrailing trip with my Fiancé. Really enjoyed our stay. There is a metro stop a couple of minutes down the road, despite the hostel not being central it didn’t matter. The room was spacious, bathrooms good and staff friendly, breakfast was okay and the food in the bar was lovely.

Main issue was the window was either fully open or not and as it was on a balcony on the Main Street we didn’t want to sleep with it open to the public so it was very hot! Also kind of annoying having people come in late/talk in the hall but I guess it comes with the territory.

This was our first hostel we stayed in during our Europe backpacking trip and after experiencing what other hostels have to offer, I can say this was the worst of the bunch. There is a bar underneath the rooms which is nice but the rooms were dirty, smelly, the windows were locked shut, and filled with high schoolers who were obviously just looking for a place to hookup.

There are too many hostels in Europe to justify staying here.

First of all, the moment I got into the reception Kira and Ashley were so welcoming. The bed was really comfortable, breakfast was great, and the night club just awesome. I had just a little problem with the plugging charger of my litter but they solved it right away. Thanks again for everything!

Amazing. The staff Pedro was very kind with us. The breakfast was good. The bedroom was cozy. The location by the river is pretty good and its very close from the metro station.

The place has a bar, a little bit expensive but with very good food

Barry is the sexiest bartender alive i love this man. great hotel wish i knew my hostel mates but still had a great time. try to spend as little
time at the hostel as possible and spend more
time around the city. still writing to meet the 200 character minimum requirement

Overall a very good hostel experience, staff encourage guests to engage with each other by organising free hostel events every evening. Pedro was really nice and helped us meet other guests.

Rooms are OK. They are very basic but as prices are cheap they are still value for money.

This was a pleasant stay. Very economical and worthwhile stay. The staff speak English so it was easy to engage them, and get help with local attractions. Reasonable
Drink and food prices in the attached bar. It’s a fairly standard hostel, multiple bunks in my room (4). They need to do a better job with lockers, the lockers are quite small (9’ x 20’). This means you can only lock up some of your stuff. They don’t have locks, or power adapters for rent/sale, so make sure you bring your own. The lockers in our room were broken, would be nice if they were fixed.

The room was clean and it seemed to be very new. I payed 20€/night inclusive breakfast. Downstairs was a nice lounge where i could study and at night people where enjoying the enclosed bar and also other bars to go out where around. Target group is probably 20-30 y.o.
They also offered a free walking tour, good wifi and reduced prices at the bar. The breakfast was modest, but they had cornflakes, and mini-baguettes so I was satisfied. The location is close to metro stations, but to walk it's a bit far from the city centre. However, I would recommend to stay there.

HI, the vibe of this hostel is IMMACULATE, simply splendid! I’ve been her a day, and I’m already having the time of my life:’)
Also, if you need a make-your-own-
mojito class teacher, LOOK FOR BARRY, he’s funsies️!!!

Had a great time at St Christopher's. The prices in Belushi bar. Especially Barry the Irish bartende! He was friendly and charismatic and very forgiving of my terrible french!! I would 100% visit again if and when I return to Paris;

As an Irish person in Paris meeting Barry from Collig behind the bar really made me feel at home and his hospitality was outstanding couldn’t have asked for anymore, I would definitely recommend this hostel and Barry behind the bar if your Irish!

The accomodation is exactly what you’d expect from a good hostel, everything is clean, relatively spacious, good wifi etc. The staff are all very helpful. The bar is definitely the best part of the place, lots of like-minded travellers hanging out, perfect place to start a night out. The bar staff are really great too, special shoutout to Barry, who was always helping introduce me to new people! Overall, ill definitely be back on my next trip to Paris :)

The place is very nice,a bit big for a hostel,not like all the small tiny hostels people are used to,location is wonderful by the canal,close to everyting and the metro,pity though with this covid thing they had to close the downstairs pub and restaurant yesterday.

nice place,great location,nice staff at the bar and security but an incredible number of problems during my stay.no shower in my private suite,no lift with 6 floors,no water during 2 days, room 's door who doesnt close,too many problems thats a shame.they gave me a 40 euros refund for that.

A clean, well organised, quiet and very very cheap hostel, about 30 min from the city centre with the metro (which is not much, considering the size of Paris). The breakfast is included if you book on their website and they have a very nice bar/pub at the ground floor. The neighbourhood is quite calm and for what I have seen not dangerous.
The common bathrooms are clean and there are many.
I would definitely recommend it for groups of friends that are planning a cheap but nice weekend in Paris!

COVID WARNING !
Some latin staff tend to allocate people of colour, regardless of attitude, in the same rooms than economically deprivated people, sometimes with doubtful hygiene and without respecting the allocation of bunkbeds with reasonable distance.
The french managers are much more inclusive and dont base their decision on skin colour only.

Be careful if you care not catching covid positive.

Had to wear a mask within a space I was paying for which ruined the experience, staff enforced this rudely and without using common sense. Having paid for a place to stay I would've thought I would have the basic human right to breathe freely and not be harassed simply for entering without a mask.

Perfect place to stay. It was very clean and calm. The staff were friendly and the food quality was almost good. The restaurant had a discount for the people staying in the hotel. Sitting near the river and drinking and talking with friends was amazing during night

Attention should be given to the steps on entry and exit to the building by the front door. No drinks should be taken beyond the steps unless the adequate seating and table facilities have been provided. Care should be taken at all times on entry and exit of the St Christopher Hostel

I got my bag stolen at the hostel and told the reception about it when I left, in case they find it back at some point.
They called me on the same evening to tell me that they found it.
I called them back on the next day, to inform them that a friend of mine would pick it up.When my friend came, they told him that they threw the bag away...Then I called them everyday, always getting the same answer "sorry but I don't personally know about this issue, please call back tomorrow", until I finally got an email address to which I had to write (of course, two times...), to get the following answer " since you didn't respond to our message, we threw the bag away".
I find it extremely dishonest and irespectul.

I’ve stayed at St Christopher Inn Canal in Paris in August 2020. It’s not far from metro and and attractions are easily reached. Views of the Canal are beautiful and morning coffee at downstairs bar terrace is a pleasant start to a busy day.. My room was clean, had towels changed and bathroom cleaned daily. All the precautions for Covid-19 are implemented. Hand sanitation stations are plenty,. Wearing face mask in downstairs premises is compulsory: bar, reception, cleaning team and security are wearing face covering at all times. The crew is very friendly and helpful, will go an extra mile to make sure they deliver excellent service.
Now, the only drawback is that there’s no small fridge in private en-suite rooms which is a complete disappointment. Usually August in Paris have a heat wave as this year too. The temperatures were reaching almost +40 C on the daily basis, the heat was unbearable . Of course there’s no air conditioning, after all it’s just a hostel. In such high temperatures not providing this little luxury for private en-suite rooms is a big disappointment. If you’re looking for a longer stay ie. up to a week or over during hot, French summer and you don’t mind any of the above mentioned then that’s your place. If you’re looking for short stay in a clean, friendly place near shops with great metro connections then this is a place for you too.
Btw my tv was broken, reception tried to fix it but sadly couldn’t. Would’ve been nice to watch a bit of news and metro at late night.

Super histle, very Clean, friendly and helping stuff, with a bar with TV, soccer, hamburgers and other stuff, renting knives etc, whatever you wish, positive people and stuff, great location near the river, where at the evenening people come and sit and enjoy the day/evening, nearby Velib rent-a-bikes 50m from entry of hostel, Metro about 300k, restaurants nearby, also stores, bakery, swimming in Siena River 300m away, piecefully inside, busy and fun outside, since many bars by the river around, also pretty near all parts of Paris that are important. Inside smart offers for whatever person needs, forgot a towel-borrow one, same with locker, sleepers, etc., a hostel that is being Developed according to the peoples needs, would highly recommend it! Thanks for a Gr8 stay and fun time, have enjoyed it as max as possible 😊😉

Eiffel Tower 10km, Moulen Rouge etc. 4km,busy City center etc. 5km, all near with a bike/Metro/Bus...
Have missed only kitchen, but bar gave me all I need, cannot say a negative word, since developed better than most hotels.

Good size bedrooms with powerpoints, cutains, comfortable beds and cleaned every day. Bathrooms could be tidied up. Breakfast tasty. Good security. Friendly helpful staff. Location interesting, metro not far away.

It was fine, the tables were sticky (not just some, literally all of the tables were sticky and all the time) and it was pretty expansive.. But the rest was OK i guess. Good connection to the city also.

I really liked the hotel and the staffs are super friendly and speak a lot of languages so the communication is easy. the room was very clean the only thing that i didn't like is that there is not toiletry in like shampoo ...

The place is clean and kept well. Maybe separate men from women for privacy. I will come back again. I like the light through the rooms. Ventilation system may be a good idea. Otherwise, it is good place to spend time in France.

I stayed for only 1 night but the experience was very good. Usually, hostels are not the place where you would like to stay more but this time I wished I didn’t book my next place. As I arrived in front of the building, the entrance was visible, but it goes through the bar called Belushi´s. The ambiance at the reception was welcoming, and I loved how lively the bar downstairs was. The food was amazing and had very competitive prices. If you are staying at the hostel, you get a bracelet that entitles you to 25% off your bill for food and drinks.

Full Review on my blog, link in bio.

I stayed two nights . This was my first stayed in a hostel. I liked it. It was good and clean room. Cheap Price and good quality foods good accommodation , comfortable beds. Nice coffe and pub. Good location , helpfull staff . Only I had to say the shower does not work properly. Always stop each one minute . There was a button You have to touch it always and always . I thought that it is for cost saving.

Very clean, excellent location, staff are amazing and the food and drink is great. Definitely recommended. Comfortable beds and showers were excellent. Stunning location next to river , luggage room is very helpful!

I loved the room: great beds with USB chargers and electric plugs for every bed. But the woman who checked us in was mean, and she didn't even speak French. I think she was Spanish. We decided to leave and go to another hostel.

The place looks nice and also is in the inside. The room was normal, comfy beed, enough space to lock up your things, shower ok. The bar was better than spected, the food very nice, all the drinks you may want, prices ok. Enough tourist information, and the people nice and helpful.
Wanna make a special mention to Alvaro, who is from Argentina, realy help me during my trip!
Will return one day!

Best waiter ever, very active, always running everywhere to serve and satisfy everyone, puts a lot of energy in his work, Yves is really qualified, funny and speaks good English, and does really good music by the way... !

Cute hostel, nice bar, service super-lame. The the elevator was broken when I was there. I have a bad back & chose this hotel as description stated elevator + good for people with mobility issues, but when the elevator broken, they took no steps to make-up for thi. I asked for help at reception: woman working there told me to buzz-off - tough-luck about the elevator. FYI she couldn't speak French, surprising at a bg Paris hostel. The younger staff (I met in the bar) were nicer (and they speak French). There's a free breakfast which was 'average'. Rooms interesting: Pod-beds wth plugs. Wifi works. It's in the seedier part of Paris, but I didn't feel unsafe. If they hired new staff, and fixed their elevator, it'd be a better place.

NEVER STAY HERE. A few months ago I was staying a few days in Paris. I stayed in the Hostel St. Christopher, and while I was there, my Dad almost died. I got a facebook message while I was in my bed at night, in a room full of people. I jumped up and as I needed to call a hospital and my family members, I went to the reception. I told the guy(s) two of them on-duty what happened.

They shrugged at me, and told me all the common areas were closed. I didn't want to sit in the stairway, so I asked if I they could please sit on the couch and talk on the phone. I was clearly upset. The guy working was Spanish and had light brown hair, a white t-shirt and a pot-belly: He seemed to be very comfortable there, like he was a senior employee or a boss. He was extremely rude.

He was talking to a friend, and that was apparently the most important thing to him. He said everything was closed and he want back to talking with his friend.

So I sat outside, and I called my home-country, and talked to hospital staff, while standing outside in the cold. In winter.

The rooms are ok, the bathrooms are dirty, the breakfast isn't anything special. But what I'll remember about this hostel is how I was treated, and I wouldn't even recommend it to someone I didn't like.

This hostel is a little further out than it’s sister hotel at Gare du Nord but is still very easy to get to via crimeé station. The bunks are very sturdy so movement through the night doesn’t make noise. The beds are comfy. Each bed comes with a light and multiple plug in spots AND USB spots. And each bed space has large metal cages to store your bags which can be locked with a padlock. The staff are incredibly helpful. Book direct and get the free continental breakfast - it’s basic but also free! Would definitely return.

I spent there 3 nights this weekend. Hostel is really clean, staff is really nice and helpful, and rooms are bright, fresh and big.
Downstairs there is a nice bar and restaurant and every night something is happening so u are never alone 🙂
Location is also really nice 20+mins to the city center with metro, really simple.
Recommend!!
🙂

The location is great, breakfast for 5 euros and very good. The restrooms could be cleaned with some more frequency, but still were very good with warm water. The atmosphere is great with a very nice bar with good prices. There is no kitchen to cook your own food. Super recommend this hostel :)

I stayed a night in St Christopher's Inn Canal Paris and had a rather mixed experience. On the one side, the amenities are great, new and clean. The right services are proposed and the staff useful. My only issue is that the surroundings of the hotel are noisy at night and the isolation not good enough to absorb such noise. Also, the room had very big windows on a whole wall, great during the day, but without blind, that makes the night too bright to have a good sleep.

A bartender named Yves gave some of the best customer service I have received anywhere- he is a gentleman and his service was great (friendly, fun and he honestly made my stay that little bit better)! This man deserves a raise!

Yves is my favourite bartender ever, like10/10 recommend, he’s amazing, give him a rise and a promotion because he’s WORTH IT. So nice, what a darling. The best ever. Literally give him a raise, do it

A big nice friendly hostel! The rooms were big and had lockers. It’s close to gare de nord which is good. The staff is very friendly and the bar and restaurant was also good. Had a very pleasant stay!

I go Paris once a year. I been coming here every year and stay here its the best Hostel in Paris. Please book through there wed side you get Free breakfast. Please bring your own Locker and Towel. I stay on the 4th floor. 4 bed only. Wonderful staff and friendly.
I be back next year. Thank you everyone.

Stayed here one night. Comfy bed and clean bedding. Although I did wake up to a wasp in my bunk! Not sure who was visiting me or the wasp?
There was a bad smell in the hallway to the room, most of the time, had to hold my breathe.

Bar downstairs is really good and comes alive in the evening with hostel visitors and locals. Good vibes and great food.
Staff are friendly and the lockers downstairs super helpful to leave stuff after check-out time.

All round an okay stay, just a bit of a clean needed to make it better.

A great hostel located next to a canal. Rooms and toilets were clean. I liked that there were curtains on the beds in the dorm rooms, gave lots of privacy! Great restaurant here with outstanding food, along with a nice bar. The only downfall to this place is that it isn’t located in the centre it’s around 4 miles from the Eiffel tower and the rooms smell a bit of dirty socks (also read this on some other reviews). But overall - great place, would recommend.

Hostel was pretty to easy to find and close to a metro station. The staff are friendly and helpful. I also like that you get free breakfast if book direct; although the breakfast wasn't very interesting. I liked that they had activity nights so on the first night there was free pasta and the second night was a film night with free popcorn - great way to meet people. Unfortunately the other 2 nights the activities never happened despite being advertised.

The dorm room and bathroom were both fine; comfy bed, privacy curtain, charging point per bed and locker for belongings.

My only real issue with the place is the noise of the traffic from the road outside and the noise from the bar downstairs. Because there's no aircon the window needed to be open and there was constant sirens, horns honking, drunk people talking loudly outside - it made it difficult to get a decent nights sleep.

It was quite easy to arrive to this hostel from the airport using subway transportation. The directions given by the hostel are clear and concise. Upon arrival, the hostel upgraded us from a dorm to a private room, which was so kind of them. The canal is beautiful and has great bars and some boat rides available. Staff is multilingual, which is always appreciated. There is a sports bar below the hostel with local beer that tastes great. Recommend this hostel!

Stayed here just one night in a 12 bed mixed dorm, room was very spacious and curtains provided good privacy but watch your head in the bunks as they are a little low! Nearest metro was about 8mins walk with a small supermarket nearby. All staff seemed busy and breakfast was basic but quality. Only issue, mens bathroom was on opposite end of my room down a long corridor. Its a big hostel. The receptionists were polite and approachable. There was an American girl who I found to be quite pleasant! Good hostel

We booked for 2 nights in 6 beds women floor,it was safe and clean,wifi good,the bfast was just basic.friendly staff,,just bring big locks for the safety box under your bed,need to deposit money for your towel.the lake was dirty,if you Don’t have problem with dorm place with too many backpackers youngsters.then it’s best place for you.but it’s far from all tourist attractions.

Paris is no easy city for any tourist, and this hostel was a great homebase. The incredible staff helped with every imaginable request or question, going far above and beyond the call of duty. Large as the hostel may be, it runs like clockwork. It's clean, it vibrant, and there's always something going on. It's basically been my nightlife during my stay in Paris, and I was completely happy with that. Also, when Agoda screwed up my reservation to a criminal degree (charged me $321 for 5 nights in a private room, then paid the hotel half to book me in a 8-person dorm), the hotel's own staff went to war for me against Agoda. They spent hours on the phone with Agoda's truly evil customer service staff, and allowed me to use their landline while I waited more hours on hold as well. Essentially, they helped me through the booking nightmare of a lifetime (never use Agoda under ANY circumstances!) I can't recommend the place enough, but book it directly via the hostel itself.

I had a very good experience visiting this hostel. It had a beautiful placement right by the canal. The banks were filled with people at night, so the life in the area was amazing. The common area was also very lively and a great place to make friends. The only problem would be, that it was far from the center (which gave me the opportunity to explore some non-touristy spots, which was really nice), and you have to take a metro to get there. Plus, the neighbourhood didn’t necessarily seem like the safest area to walk around alone at night...

This hostel was good. The showers were alittle annoying, you have to push a button for water every some odd seconds, water was hot though, but everything else was great, from the food to the curtains on the beds. The staff was pretty nice. I did not use the laundry though.

We stayed here for 6 days during a heat wave in Paris, so the rooms were hot. They didn’t have any fans which made the circulation of air unbearable at times. The rooms are big and the curtains are nice, except they trap the heat. The showers could use a shelf for your items, but it’s only a slight inconvenience. The free breakfast is limited, but free, which is a plus. It’s only free if you book through their website though. I was given a key card that barely worked and when I complained she told me it was the lock on the door, but my friend had no issues with hers. I was disappointed they didn’t listen to me and just give me a working card. At some point it just stopped working all together and was then finally given a replacement. They have a strict one person per bed policy, which is great, until one of your bunkees brings home a boy and security barges in and flips on the light at 3am to kick him out. Overall, I enjoyed the location, the size of the room and the cleanliness. But I probably wouldn’t stay here again.

As the caption mentions, its an amazing hostel at an affordable price range just 400 mts from the metro station and situated just besides the canal which makes it accessible for a breezy evening stroll. We had taken a private room which had a sharing bathroom but nonetheless never had any problem. The staff was very helpful, forthcoming and suggested us places to visit . Though a bit far from the city center e.g Eiffel tower is around 35-40 minutes by metro but metro connectivity is very good. The place is quite safe and we never had any problem or encounters with pickpockets as heard.

When I checked in at 230, the sheets had not been changed, but when I came back around 630 it had been fixed. Good easy access, storage for belongings under the bed, 2 outlets per bed. Showers due have a timer on them, but it is not too bad. It is a bit far from the city centre, but close to several metro locations. There was a sink in the room which was nice. I was able to check out at 630am with no problems. The room its self was large and spacious even in a dorm with 10 beds.

Okay, so this was the last Hostel Experience ive had during my Euro Trip and I must say it was the best. The place is extremely clean, staff are friendly, and the environment is modern. The bar/food areas are exceptional, storage units in the room are appropriate, the beds were pretty comfortable, and the privacy curtain gave it extra Flavor. Wrist Bands were provided at check in to receive discounts on food and drinks. The Location is very convenient to public trans and eateries. My only complaint is that the room can get pretty warm. Once you open the window, you should be fine. Also, the lift is a little slow so taking the stairs is sometimes the best bet. Other than that, i would definitely recommend thia Place!!

I checked in at 4.30pm and found my bed sheets & pillows dirty with black spots on them. I told the reception guy 3 times and every time he says someone will change them right now. It took them 1.5hrs to change my bed sheets! Horrible...and reception reply is "cleaning staff has other things to do!" .

I spent New Years Eve in this hostal with 9 friends and it was the best decision that we made. The ST Christopher Inn is a hostal young adults that want to have a good time. our room was for 8 people and we had our own space with a curtain. The Hostal has a bar on the first floor that everynight we would go to and have a great time with a discount on drinks and food for staying in the St Christopher Inn. They threw a New Years Eve Party that we stayed in until 4 am.

Clean and comfy beds, and the washrooms and showers were very tidy. Shemayan and the other staff were awesome, and great free social events to get everybody mingling. Definitely coming back next time I’m in Paris.

Good choice to save some money. But don't forget to carry a secure locker so that you can put your bags protected, otherwise you will have to rent or buy one.
Bathrooms are clean, and outside the view is very nice and quiet to walk.

Great location next to the canal with a balcony overlooking the water. The canal is a hub of activity during holidays in the summer - boats, yachts, people hanging out at the bank, picnicking. The hostel is clean and huge.

(1) LOCATION: next to canal. 3 blocks fr Metro.
(2) BUNK PRIVACY: curtains, lamp, socket.
(3) BATHROOMS cleaned > once a day.

(-) Dorm bedroom doors DONT LOCK automatically. You must manually lock the door. I'm in a 12 man dorm. How many ppl will manually lock the door? I told front desk about it. They said that's the way it is.

Sure enough the next day a guy comes into my 5th F dorm room & lies down on the sofa. After 30 min I asked him what he was doing. He said waiting for a friend. I told him to wait downstairs. He accused me of lacking the hostel "spirit" & began eating chips & cookies belonging to others. I packed all of my stuff & went downstairs to tell staff.

(-) All of the electrical sockets are LOOSE. If you have to use a converter AND your charging unit, they will fall off. The electrical sockets are loose from overuse. Additionally they are located a meter high. I have to build a tower to support my charger.

Mgmt never apologized about the intruder, even after they sent me an email asking about my stay. St Christopher's is getting too big for its breeches.

It’s amazing what they do this guys. They really have a great hostel overall.

Located a little bit up north in the city, has an amazing view to the canal, a very good restaurant and a superb staff. They really make you feel at home. Specially a girl from Sri Lanka 🇱🇰 and a guy from Argentina 🇦🇷. On the welcome drink (that btw is a great idea for integrating new guests) they really make us enjoy the day (and during the stay they also did it).

It’s a lil bit huge in my opinion, but anyway it’s great. Well equipped the rooms with storage for your bags. And the burgers are the resl deal st the resto.

Basically has an amazing vibe. Congrats

The check in was ok. You have to pay a deposit for your key card, that will be returned once you hand your key card back in. The rooms were big, with a table and chair in the centre. In the morning I had my own breakfast, and just needed some hot water to add to my porridge, which they provided along with cutlery, but I was put in a separate room, I do understand why, but I did not like the way you are separated from others. This place is close to the metro. I have stayed at St Christopher's Inn Village - London Bridge in London, and this one was better.

Excellent staff! Friendly, helpful and welcoming. Great security, have lots of cameras and security at front door. every 7pm is free drinks to meet and greet with people. tours in the mornings around paris. comfy beds with privacy curtains. excellent food as well!!
SAM + GUARAB are AWEWOME!!! Super nice bartenders, very friendly! So glad we stayed here, very nice customer service, bice people and great music, food and drinks. Definitely recommend! I love! 🙏💛😇🥂🍻

I stayed for 4 nights in a twin private room February 2019. The hostel is clean, well organized and has helpful staff. At times, especially during peak hours, there was a long line up to speak to a receptionist so perhaps adding more staff would be helpful. The breakfast was very good. I would suggest a few more options for Gluten Free items for those with sensitivities to wheat as I could not eat any of the bread or cereals offered. The mattresses and bedding were comfortable and the room, although small, was well laid out. I participated in a "free" walking tour and it was excellent. It wasn't free however, as the guide expects to be tipped at the end so be prepared to spend about 10 Euros for the 2 hour tour.

The hostel has a good lounge area and the bar is always hopping with people day and night which is great to meet people. It would be nice to have a sink and some dish-ware available in the lounge to wash cups, get tap water etc.

My major complaint was the noise. The hostel is located on a busy street and you can hear the traffic and sirens day and night. There are also people in the hallways constantly talking on cell phones and you hear room doors open and slam shut. I could also hear the people in the room above me which sounded like they were bowling. I would stay there again, but would ask for a quieter floor and room location.

Well situated with nice surroundings, the staff are friendly and helpful, the rooms are ok but make sure to let the windows open as much as you can to move the air because 6 persons sleeping in one room with the shoes and everything can be a pit smelly, the bathrooms are clean and tidy

Hostel was amazing, clean and nice place to stay. Canal was good with a nice view but was smelly and litter was in the canal. People sat there at night to have drinks but left the bottles. I think canal should be cleaned regularly.

I loved the room and the ablutions at this place, it has a lively clean ambience. The common area is fabulous and I loved that I could watch the football games. Lifts all worked perfectly. I felt safe there and it is very well located, close to everything you need. The breakfasts were super and the one dinner we had there was very goo and reasonably priced

Everything goes very smooth at this hostel. They have a really good system and tons of perks: downstairs bar, weekend nightclub underground, lounge area, curtains for each bed, and much, much more.

Make sure to book through their website for free breakfast.

Special shoutout to the reception staff; Lautaro, Myllon, Hayden, and Thom!! They helped me every time I needed assistance or wanted a recommendation.

I stayed here for one night between cities and it was fairly nice. I had brought a lock from home, however the lock I brought was not long enough for the cages in the room. So I had to buy one from reception, so be aware of that. The rooms were clean, and it was nice having a sink in the room although the toilet and showers are in the common areas. Though the aforementioned toilets and showers did have a men's and a women's (i.e. Not co-ed). There is a great map of Paris in the reception/common area, and there's a fair amount of seating space in the common area/bar. There was also a balcony, but I didn't explore as it was December! There are also pay lockers in the basement to store your luggage before or after your stay, which I wasn't too impressed with, most hostels have a free luggage room. That's one of my very few cons.

I stayed here in 2016 for the first time, back again for the NWE2018/2019. 4 nights is the period I stayed this time. So far, everything was almost very good except some details:
1. The access from and back to the room is still complicated
2. Elevator take too long
3. Staff less friendly than back in 2016

Great breakfast with a good value for money, intimacy in the room guaranteed, I still recommend it.

Came here for Christmas 2018 with my cousin. Our private room was all that we needed, good value and clean. The staff at the front desk and bar downstairs were super friendly and chatty. It was really nice to see they were putting on a Christmas meal which a lot of people attended (we didn't unfortunately). Only requests would be for the bar to close less early (it was full then suddenly everyone was kicked out!) and the showers to be a bit less annoying (having to push it every 30s was a pain but I understand the need to conserve water). Definitely would recommend, location was really great too, very atmospheric on the canal and literally a two minute walk from the metro.

My experience was very decent. The Hostel is located on a canal, close to the city Centre. The accommodation is adequate & comfortable. The food served at the restaurant downstairs is good! Try the burger special!

Lastly, the staff & management are extremely helpful, very friendly & speak a multitude of languages!

Accommodation is perfect if you looking for an in and out clean spot to stay in! Also a good bar and restaurant downstairs if you tired from the day exploring! We stayed in a room for 8 people and it actually was perfect!

St. Christopher’s Canal Paris ticks all of the boxes for a hostel: safety/security, affordability, location and friendly staff. The hostel shares a lobby with Belushi’s (a rather rowdy watering hole). However, a keycard is needed to access the hostel wing, as well as each room. There are private curtains on all beds to provide privacy, and the storage lockers underneath the beds are convenient. The price is good because it is not in the city centre. However, there are two metro stops within walking distance. Lastly, the staff (especially Ana) is multilingual, attentive and genuinely helpful. The front desk sells padlocks (for your storage locker), outlet adapters and toiletries. Continental breakfast and pints of ‘Frog’s Bollocks’ are an affordable 4€ at Belushi’s if you flash your room card!

I stayed at this place for 2 nights. I would recommend this for stay if you are solo or backpack travellers. If you book directly you'll get free breakfast. It's Very Nice overall and View is also quite good.

First time I stayed in a hostel and I can say it was much better than anticipated. This hostel is part of a hostel chain that has presence all over Europe and fulfilled all my needs. It conveniently has a restaurant (Belushi's) that also serves as a bar later at night and it features a club downstairs. Though I read that it can get noisy on the weekends due to all the partying going on I did not hear any disturbance in my room and did not have any issues sleeping. Check in is at 2 and check out is at 11. Note: staying here gives you a 25% discount on food at Belushi's and if you book directly from St Christopher's website, you get free continental breakfast that may be simple but filling. In all, If you are backpacking and need a decent place to sleep and shower, this place can be a firm candidate.

This place sets the bar high for hostels! The food is brilliant and so reasonably priced too. Rooms are so modern and clean as well and a great location. Very chill atmosphere. Will definitely be returning!!

Fabulous service accommodation staff ambiance reasonably priced u can party dine drink or sleep. Electronic key lifts and women only floor Set on a beautiful canal with a deck to watch ducks boats and people or chat to fellow guests.
The managers and staff are bi lingual and you can arrange tours etc check in on line and breakfast included

I’ll start by saying that the location is amazing, the room view is incredible, at least in the rooms I stayed in. I stayed for 3-4 days, the staff was amazing, everyone really welcoming and polite. Although I always saw the cleaning staff working, the room smell was not pleasant, same goes for the bathroom. I’m not sure if it’s a canal thing, but it didn’t smell clean. Beds are comfortable, I stayed in a room made for 12 people and still I could keep my privacy using the curtains. Bathrooms are shared, but I recommend you ask for a room near yours, cause I was on the other side of the hallway and it wasn’t fun getting there in the middle of the night when I really needed to go. Overall, great stay, the gorgeous view, great staff and location surely made my stay happier, be aware only if you think the smell thing would set you off.

Incredible hostel overall. The staff are super friendly (Hayden and Gauv are some of the nicest guys I've met - very funny). The rooms are perfect for what you are paying for, and above all else, the social aspect is top notch. I met so many new people every day in my dorm and at the bar, from all kinds of countries, so if you're travelling solo, don't worry. Definitely returning next year.

I stayed here with a friend in a shared dorm, the rooms were nice enough, clean and the beds were comfy. After the first night with a loud snoring man, we ended up as only 2 in the room for the remainder of the trip. The location was wonderful, close to the met and the canal. The bar restaurant downstairs was great, with so many people in the hostel I ended up making some friends that still after 2 years I still like to message.

We had a good stay at St Christopher's Inn Canal. Location was out of the city, but no trouble getting into central Paris. Close to a nice brewery, and the bar in the hostel itself is good fun and atmosphere. The rooms were nice, curtains were appreciated. Good if you want to be social, but kitchen ammenities for those wanting to cook their own food could have been better. Bar staff could be quite unpleasant, but hostel staff in checking in/out/asking questions were nice enough.

This is the best Hostels in Paris. I have come here every year past 9 Years. This is my 9th Stay here. If you are coming by metro come off at Crimee station line 7 go to Exit 3. I was so, happy one of the staff knew me from last year stay. I got my card key in few seconds. Has always my room was clean with light, curtain and power points. There showers at the end of the hall way. Check in time is 2pm I came around 7pm.
Please bring your own pad locks, Towels and shower gel. At breakfast start from 7.30 to 10am. There lots to choses from and TV is always on sports. I love this Hostels and I be back next year. Thank you to everyone.

You probably find hostels both closer to major attractions and cheaper, but this is worth it. Good service, always clean, great spread for breaky (book direct and get for free), and once you work out the metro it’s easy to get places. Area can seem a bit gritty at night, but the locals drinking in the park mind their own business and aren’t much interested in passer by’s.

Near Gare du Nord, ideal if you are planning to take the plane in CDG because you can straight the RER B. Lockers. Cool bar. Bathroom clean. Bed lights. And VERY cheap for Paris

This area in Paris is dodgy, many hobos on crack

We stayed in a 12 bed dorm for 3 nights and were very happy with the stay. Each bed had a light, a curtain for privacy and power points which was handy. The room was very spacious, plenty of windows for natural light and ventilation and each bed was assigned a locker for valuables. The toilets/showers were nearby on the floor and always seemed to be clean and tidy. No kitchen facilities, however, you do get discounts on food and drink downstairs at Belushis and they always have specials as well. Hostel was close to quite a few different stations on different lines and within walking distance. It is a bit of a hike to get to the main sights, however, with how big Paris is, nearly anywhere is going to be. Staff were lovely and very helpful.

My first impression was that our room smelled like old sweaty socks. Really strongly. It did for our entire stay (four nights). So we had to sleep with the windows open (I guess that was the reason?) and there was so much noice outside since this is a party hostel. I have only been to a hostel once befor so I don't relly know if this reek is an widespread problem at hostels, but the one I visited before this didn't stink so I think not.

The showers and toilet was really nice and clean (exept for the handicap toilet which smelled really bad, also the entire stay). The breakfast was HORRIBLE! Overall we had an okay stay but if I went back to Paris I don't think I would live here. Mostly because the obnoxious smell in our dorm.

For a solo traveler, this is a great hostel in terms of its social environment; the bar downstairs is very inviting and they always try to get people involved. Also, drink specials!
However - there is no kitchen. Pretty much forces you to order food downstairs or go out to eat. It's close to a metro stop but far from the sights: 45 minutes by metro to the Eiffel Tower. Not exactly ideal for a Parisian experience.

The rooms were ok, nothing special and also very hot for the summer. The female bathrooms were seemingly always out of toilet paper, which is not ideal for a woman.

Big hostel with large dorms, privacy curtain and individual lights and power was handy. Fairly close to a couple of metro stations. Good deals at the bar downstairs which had decent food. The bathrooms were pretty good. No waiting and seemed clean.
Oh the smell of the dorms though! So bad! No fans or ventilation to air out the rooms.

Never really liked this hostel. I have to stay for work and the hallways always stink and the bathrooms stink even more. It’s hot as anything in the rooms, there is no ventilation or even a fan. Peoples stuff have been stolen countless times from randoms off the street. The breakfast is so average it’s a joke. You better off renting an airBnB and just going there to drink and chill than actually stay.
